<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 15 at 1:46PM CST  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Snow showers will bring low visibility...
An area of moderate snow showers over northwest Illinois will
quickly move northeast toward Rockford Illinois by 330 PM. Expect
a period of visibility as low as 1/2 mile in snow as these pass
through. Up to a 1/2 inch of snow accumulation is expected as
well.
If you are traveling, slow down and use your lights this
afternoon. If you are able to, delay travel until after these
snow showers pass through by 330 PM.</description>
